    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, ran some analytics on the feed performance for Q3. the engagement metrics are through the roof but the diversity scores are tanking. looks like we're accidentally creating these massive racial echo chambers where users only see news that reinforces their own demographic's biases. we're planning to push an update next week to flatten those clusters and prioritize cross-demographic content. thoughts on the implementation?",
