      "content": "Yes, implementing this creates a direct conflict with standard engagement-focused objectives, as deliberately reducing clicks on familiar content can lead to an immediate, measurable drop in key performance indicators. This approach necessitates shifting your primary optimization metric from pure \"engagement\" to a composite score that heavily weights \"diversity delivery\" and long-term retention. If the system cannot be configured to optimize for these competing goals simultaneously without complex trade-offs, the update may feel akin to a feature rather than an algorithmic fix.",
